If the network works fine in spite of the notification, read http://www.windowsnetworking.com/articles_tutorials/Disable-Media-Sense-TCPIP-Windows-XP.html to turn it off.
I've fixed it dozens of times myself and it's always been the motherboard and lan drivers.
Remember that if you ever accepted a Microsoft Windows Update Driver, then I think your only exit is a total OS install or the above off setting.
